Introduction

EL7Z UP is a seven-member South Korean global project girl group signed with Apple Monster and DG Entertainment. Their name, “else-up,” means they aim to rise higher. It’s also an anagram on “PUZZLE", signifying "the best seven members the audience 'puzzled' out".

The group consists of members from various agencies and groups who competed in the Mnet reality show Queendom Puzzle, which ran from June to August 2023.

The members consist of Kei of Lovelyz, Yeeun of CLC, Yeoreum of WJSN, Yeonhee of Rocket Punch, Nana of WOOAH, Hwiseo of H1-KEY, and Yuki of PURPLE KISS

They made their official debut on September 14, 2023, with the mini album “7+Up” featuring the title track “CHEEKY”.
